Fav&Co is all about insightful, well-written product reviews by real people, much like you and me. Product reviews span a wide range of lifestyles and product categories, where craftsmanship meets perfection, pragmatism meets beauty, all in one centralized easy-to-browse place. Ever find yourself surfing the interwebs, sifting through countless Google images, mind-numbing product reviews, and less-than-relevant shopping engines for the absolute perfect whatever-it-may-be? Description: SurfCanister is security software that helps keep computers secure when browsing the internet.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: SurfCanister announced the launch of their first security product. SurfCanister is a patent pending safe browsing technology, which protects users’ computer, as well as valuable and confidential data against latest Trojans and Viruses. There are 55,000 new malware samples submitted by various organizations to AVtest.org every day. It has been really hard for Antivirus companies to keep up with sheer volume of malware variants. There is a lag between new malware comes out and Antivirus engine detect them. In this window when there are no signatures users are exposed to new viruses and Trojans (also known as Zero Day).  SurfCanister founder Sunil Shilimkar said “Instead of traditional reactive security approach, users need preventive security. SurfCanister has advanced malware protection mechanism which conventional Anti-virus softwares lack. SurfCanister runs viruses and Trojans in isolated environment and blocks malware from accessing to users confidential files and documents. SurfCanister does not need signature definitions or updates to protect users’ computer, hence users are protected 24X7.”  According to recent study published by Sophos, Web has become the biggest source for malware. More than 85% of malware comes from web. While browsing web, a lot of confidential information such as user’s credit card number, social security number, bank user name and password are stored inside web browser’s cache. Spyware can steal such valuable information stored in user’s browser other confidential locations on users’ computer.  SurfCanister isolates browser and operating system resources and gives one click option to the user to clean up isolated browsing data or operating system resources to get rid of malware foot prints as well as protects the user’s identity by cleaning the critical information such as credit card number, social security number, bank user name and passwords.   SurfCanister’s advanced protection mechanism automatically secures user’s valuable data reside inside My Documents, My Pictures, My Music folders and other personal folders while browsing. SurfCanister also allows users to select any folder(s) which has user’s valuable or confidential data.   There is a one year free trial version of SurfCanister is available for users to protect against latest threats. SurfCanister is also offering 25% discount on their final release to all its beta users. Visit www.surfcanister.com/download to download the beta product.

Full Description: Prison Legal News (PLN) is a 72-page monthly magazine that reports on criminal justice issues and prison and jail-related civil litigation, with an emphasis on prisoners’ rights. It is a project of the non-profit Human Rights Defense Center. It covers a wide range of topics that include prison labor, rape and sexual abuse, misconduct by prison and jail staff, prisoners’ constitutional rights, racial and socioeconomic disparities in the criminal justice system, medical and mental health care for prisoners, disenfranchisement, rehabilitation and recidivism, prison privatization, prison and jail phone rates, women prisoners, the Prison Litigation Reform Act (PLRA), prison censorship, the death penalty, HIV and hep C, solitary confinement and control units, and more. The monthly magazine is a subscription-based publication. It also offers website subscriptions that provide full access to all content on its website, which includes all of PLN’s articles plus thousands of other articles, case reports, publications, and pleadings. PLN also distributes a number of criminal justice, legal, and self-help books through its book store. In 2013, PLN received the First Amendment Award from the Society of Professional Journalists. Prison Legal News was launched in 1990 and its operations are based in Lake Worth, Florida.
